orbsMatch

private boolean orbsMatch(int col,
                          int extent)
                   throws ParameterException
Determines whether in a column, every group of orbitals and occupancies in the author's diagram exists also in the response.

Parameters:
col - 1-based column number
extent - whether to compare information on occupancies and number of orbitals
Returns:
true if every group of orbitals in a column of the author's diagram can be found in the response diagram
Throws:
ParameterException - if column is out of range

correlationsOK

private boolean correlationsOK(boolean ignoreE)
Determines whether the lines that connect the occupied cells in the two diagrams are the same. "Same" here means EITHER:
  • that the energy order of the occupied cells that are connected are the same within each column; e.g., the second-highest energy cell in column 2 is connected to the highest energy cell in column 3 in both diagrams, OR
  • that the energies of the occupied cells are ignored, but their contents are considered.

Parameters:
ignoreE - whether to ignore energies of occupied cells
Returns:
true if the lines connecting occupied cells are the same
